          "answer": "$f(3) = 2$",
          "solution": "$$f(3) = 2(9) - 15 - 1 = 2$$",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(2*3**2 - 5*3 - 1, 2)"
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
          "body": "Solve $f(x) = 0$, giving your answers to three significant figures.",
          "marks": 4,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "use the GDC (or the quadratic formula)"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "discriminant $25 + 8 = 33$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$x \\approx -0.186$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$x \\approx 2.69$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$x \\approx -0.186$ or $x \\approx 2.69$",
          "solution": "$$x = \\frac{5 \\pm \\sqrt{25 + 8}}{4} = \\frac{5 \\pm \\sqrt{33}}{4}$$$$x \\approx -0.186 \\text{ or } 2.69$$",
          "verify": [
            "Abs((5 - sqrt(33))/4 - (-0.186)) < 0.00051",
            "Abs((5 + sqrt(33))/4 - 2.69) < 0.0051"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "contextIntro": "The function $f$ is given by $f(x) = 2x^2 - 5x - 1$."
    },
